\begin{activity} \label{A:1.8.7} Find the curvature of the helix with parameterization $\vr(t) = \cos(t) \vi + \sin(t) \vj + t \vk$.



\begin{comment}

Here we have
\[\vr'(t) = (-\sin(t)) \vi + \cos(t) \vj + \vk\]
and
\[\vT(t) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\left( (-\sin(t)) \vi + \cos(t) \vj + \vk \right).\]
Then
\[\vT'(t) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\left( (-\cos(t)) \vi - \sin(t) \vj \right)\]
and so
\[\kappa(t) = \frac{1}{2}.\]

\end{comment}

\end{activity}
